Interface Configurable<C extends Configurable<C>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Resettable<C>, Specifiable<C>, Specified, Typed
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    _3DGUI, Area, BackgroundWidget, BaseShape, BorderWidget, Button, CheckBox, ConfigurableElement, ConfigurationElement, Console, Container, Cuboid, Frame, Grid, GUI, HorizontalLine, HorizontalStack, InvisibleGUI, JMonkeyMainFrame, Label, Line, MainFrame, MultiShape, SelectionMenu, Shape, SingleContainer, Sphere, Stack, TabContainer, TextBox, TextLineWidget, VerticalLine, VerticalStack, VisibleGUI, Widget

    public interface Configurable<C extends Configurable<C>>
extends Specifiable<C>
    A configurable object is a specifiable object that: -has a type and super types -can have a name -can have a group -can contain other configurable objects The default methods of this interface need not to be overwritten.
